Bankers Trust Co is raising 200 mlndlrs through an offering of subordinated equity contract notesdue 1997 with an eight pct coupon and par pricing, said leadmanager Shearson Lehman Brothers Inc.    That is 87 basis points more than the yield of comparableTreasury securities.    Non-callable to maturity, the issue is rated Aa-3 byMoody's Investors Service Inc and AA by Standard and Poor'sCorp. Salomon Brothers Inc co-managed the deal. Reuter&#3;